      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The heavy oak door clicked shut, leaving only the murmur of the air conditioning. \"It’s the restlessness of the young ones,\" one man sighed into his tumbler of bourbon, swirling the amber liquid. \"They simply lack the appreciation for the quiet dignity of how this town has always been run.\" Another leaned forward, steepling his fingers. \"Dignity, yes, but they are stirring up trouble where there should only be calm. We'll need a firmer hand, a more visible presence down near the edge of town.\" The third nodded slowly, a faint, condescending smile touching his lips. \"Protection, gentlemen. That’s what we’re offering them—a gentle guidance back to the proper path.\"",
      "source": "target",
